title: [Whistler's Pass, Creek]
description: A pair of weeping willows droop across the creek from opposite banks, their limbs forming a curtain across the creek.  Fireflies flit in and out of the willow trees, their nighttime homes disturbed by your passing.
A pair of weeping willows droop across the creek from opposite banks, their limbs forming a curtain across the creek.  Dragonflies flit in and out of the willow trees.
